  <div>
    <p>If you have a Gumroad account, you can easily move your downloads to your Dropbox:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Log into your <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/login">Dropbox account</a>.</li>
      <li>Go to <a href="http://www.gumroad.com/library">your Gumroad library</a> and click on the product that you’d like to send to Dropbox. You can also go to the download link in your email receipt.</li>
      <li>Click “Download all”, then “Save to Dropbox” from the dropdown on the top-right. Since you are logged into Dropbox, you will be able to choose the folder where you want to store the files.</li>
    </ol>
